<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-07-11T21:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-07-11T21:00:00-05:00" n="401" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d401">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">763.72/1965½: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">President <persName type="from">Wilson</persName> to
                                Mr. J. P. Tumulty</hi> (<gloss type="to"><hi rend="italic">Secretary
                                    to the President</hi></gloss>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Windsor, Vt.</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-07-11T21:00:00-05:00">
                                    <hi rend="italic">July 11, 1915—9 p. m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>According to our telephone conversation shall not expect Secretary of
                            State to come here without previous consultation with me as to the best
                            plan for conference.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Woodrow Wilson</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>